Bank of Sharjah (BOS)  climbed to the
highest level in more than a year as the United Arab Emiratesâ€™
lender buys back shares.  The stock jumped 4.2 percent to 1.99 dirhams, the highest
level since March 2010, at 10:44 a.m. in Abu Dhabi. The
benchmark  ADX General Index (ADSMI)  climbed 0.2 percent.  The bank bought back 3.68 million shares yesterday and has
regulatory approval to purchase a further 96 million shares, it
said in a statement to the Abu Dhabi bourse today. Bank of
